\item for every $(sailboat,crosswind) \in \RR^2$, the vector $\nabla moonlight(sailboat,crosswind)$ is either $\mathbf{0}$ or parallel to the vector $\langle buttercup(sailboat), -buttercup(crosswind) \rangle$.
